nerViewController’ and its subclasses."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Sometimes it is necessary to limit a live video frame detection or recognition to a certain rectangular area with"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a specific aspect ratio: the region or rectangle of interest. This is where a view finder comes in."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It crops the video frame to that region of interest before passing it to any scanner. Usually"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the performance of scanners gain a benefit from it because less pixels must be processed."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Additionally, to guide the user, the view finder visualizes the region of interest by drawing a rectangle around"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"on the user interface."}]},"doc://net.doo.ScanbotSDK/documentation/ScanbotSDK":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/net.doo.ScanbotSDK\/documentation\/ScanbotSDK","url":"\/documentation\/scanbotsdk","title":"ScanbotSDK","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Version: 8.0.2"}],"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","role":"collection"}},"variantOverrides":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}],"patch":[{"path":"\/identifier\/interfaceLanguage","op":"replace","value":"occ"},{"path":"\/metadata\/roleHeading","op":"replace","value":"Instance Property"},{"path":"\/metadata\/title","op":"replace","value":"preferredHeight"},{"value":"property","op":"replace","path":"\/metadata\/symbolKind"},{"value":[{"text":"preferredHeight","kind":"identifier"}],"op":"replace","path":"\/metadata\/fragments"},{"value":null,"op":"add","path":"\/topicSections"},{"value":null,"op":"add","path":"\/relationshipsSections"},{"value":null,"op":"add","path":"\/seeAlsoSections"},{"value":{"declarations":[{"languages":["occ"],"tokens":[{"text":"@property","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" (","kind":"text"},{"text":"nonatomic","kind":"keyword"},{"text":") ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIde